<li>Philosophically what is being asserted by this blank slate reference?</li>
<li>The assertion is made that "If the brain ceases &#x2026; nothing is left, not us &#x2026;" While we have certainly seen a lot of evidence that the brain is central to consciousness, have we seen anything to say that the brain is all of consciousness? Are we inferring absence from absence of evidence?</li>
